program1.2:-
(1) Define VariousJava Scrip terms.
(a) JS Statements (b) JS Syntax
(c)JS Keywords  (d) JS Comments

ans:-(a) JS Statements
 JavaScript statements are individual instructions that tell the browser what action to perform. Each statement usually ends with a semicolon (;).
 Example:
let x = 10;

(b) JS Syntax
 JavaScript syntax refers to the set of rules that defines how JavaScript programs are written and structured. It includes rules for variables, operators, functions, and statements.
 Example:
let name = "John";
(c) JS Keywords
 JavaScript keywords are reserved words that have special meanings and cannot be used as variable or function names.
 Examples: let, var, const, if, else, for, while, function, return.
(d) JS Comments
 JavaScript comments are used to explain code or make it more readable. They are ignored by the browser during execution.
 Types of comments:
Single-line comment: // This is a comment

Multi-line comment:

/* This is
   a multi-line comment */


